body:
The below example causes an assertion failure: `` netlist.cc:822: failed assertion indices.size()+1 == packed_dims().size() ``.
```Verilog
module top;
    wire [3:0][2:0] arr;
    assign arr[2+:2] = 1;
endmodule
```
However, the following equivalent example is accepted cleanly.
```Verilog
module top;
    wire [3:0][2:0] arr;
    assign arr[3:2] = 1;
endmodule
```

Removing the least significant dimension (`[2:0]`) also allows the original example to be accepted. The crash persists with more dimensions added.

code_blocks:
module top;
    wire [3:0][2:0] arr;
    assign arr[2+:2] = 1;
endmodule

module top;
    wire [3:0][2:0] arr;
    assign arr[3:2] = 1;
endmodule
